  "copy": {
    "caption": "Australia's tallest bird, with the father doing almost everything.",
    "shortDescription": "Emus are big, shaggy, and surprisingly fast — they can hit fifty kilometers per hour on open ground. When emu eggs are laid, the father takes charge: he stops eating and drinking and sits on the nest for eight weeks straight, losing a third of his body weight by the time the chicks hatch. Emus can't fly, but they are strong swimmers and will cross rivers without hesitation. Fun fact: Emus have two sets of eyelids — one for blinking and one to keep out dust and sand."
